{
  "text": "Autism spectrum disorder (ASD) is a family of neurodevelopmental disorders with a wide range of sensory and socio-emotional deficits [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Empathy, the ability to share vicariously the feelings of others, is an important socialemotional faculty [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] and is compromised in individuals with ASD [BaronCohen and Wheelwright, 2004] . Empathy is considered a multifaceted construct, including at least emotional contagion and arousal and cognitive perspective-taking [CITATION_5] . Previous studies have demonstrated abnormalities in various aspects of empathy in individuals with ASD, including difficulties in mentalizing and perspectivetaking [CITATION_6] MinioPaluello et al., 2009] , as well as heightened affective arousal to emotional stimuli [CITATION_7] . However, there has not been a mechanistic account for these socio-emotional deficits in ASD.",
